12
00:00:38,000 --> 00:00:40,399
What are you doing here?

13
00:00:40,399 --> 00:00:42,600
Well, this is gonna sound lame. Saving you guys?

14
00:00:42,600 --> 00:00:43,799
I don't know.

15
00:00:43,799 --> 00:00:47,799
We were coming to rescue you and bring magic back to the world.

16
00:00:47,799 --> 00:00:49,600
Oh, delightful. Excellent.

17
00:00:49,600 --> 00:00:51,200
Do me first. Do me first.

18
00:00:51,200 --> 00:00:53,200
And you are?

19
00:00:53,200 --> 00:00:57,000
Didn't you recognize me in my fine janitor outfit?

20
00:00:57,000 --> 00:00:59,400
Just a janitor over here.

21
00:01:00,399 --> 00:01:03,600
That's what I thought.

22
00:01:03,600 --> 00:01:04,599
Fucking janitor.

23
00:01:04,599 --> 00:01:07,599
I'm gonna go knock on Bahamut's cell.

24
00:01:07,599 --> 00:01:10,400
The old man, he naps through everything.

25
00:01:10,400 --> 00:01:21,200
Yenbul goes behind Sirik and then just like plants herself and pushes as hard as she can.

26
00:01:21,200 --> 00:01:22,200
Clerics!

27
00:01:22,200 --> 00:01:29,000
With you all huddled close, we see him blink.

28
00:01:29,000 --> 00:01:33,000
As you all teleport out of the prison.

29
00:01:38,200 --> 00:01:39,799
Welcome to Dumbgeons and Dragons.

30
00:01:39,799 --> 00:01:41,200
I'm your Dungeon Master Russ More.

31
00:01:41,200 --> 00:01:43,400
He, him. Also with me today is Amy More.

32
00:01:43,400 --> 00:01:51,200
I am here and I play Thea Amastasia, a female high elf druid and we both go by she, her.

33
00:01:51,200 --> 00:01:52,799
And Carla Maxted.

34
00:01:52,799 --> 00:01:54,000
She, her.

35
00:01:54,000 --> 00:01:57,000
I'm playing Yen Bolnuri, a Kalishtar cleric.

36
00:01:57,000 --> 00:01:58,599
Also she, her.

37
00:01:58,600 --> 00:02:00,200
And Tom Laird's here.

38
00:02:00,200 --> 00:02:01,000
He, him.

39
00:02:01,000 --> 00:02:08,800
And I am playing Tulgier Heavyfoot, a mountain dwarf pAlydin who I don't know where to go with that sentence.

40
00:02:08,800 --> 00:02:11,000
Who is a cool guy?

41
00:02:11,000 --> 00:02:12,200
Cool guy.

42
00:02:12,200 --> 00:02:13,400
It's a real cool guy.

43
00:02:13,400 --> 00:02:16,400
I somehow have blanked out that his last name was Heavyfoot.

44
00:02:16,400 --> 00:02:17,200
Yeah.

45
00:02:17,200 --> 00:02:22,000
That seemed like brand new information to me, which it definitely wasn't.

46
00:02:22,000 --> 00:02:26,200
Which Tulgier is a patron named character.

47
00:02:26,200 --> 00:02:31,000
So thank you, Christian Brown, for naming Tulgier Heavyfoot for us.

48
