81
00:03:43,599 --> 00:03:55,799
An icy, stale wind blows across the city of Bryn Shander as our group appears in an

82
00:03:55,799 --> 00:03:57,000
illuminated shudder.

83
00:03:57,000 --> 00:04:08,000
The city is destroyed, flattened to the ground.

84
00:04:08,000 --> 00:04:16,600
Thea, Yenbul, Talgir, Agoth and Rax huddle around the recovering human form of Bahamut.

85
00:04:16,600 --> 00:04:22,399
He looks frail and disheveled and begins to collapse after having teleported the group

86
00:04:22,399 --> 00:04:23,399
back to Corsair.

87
00:04:23,399 --> 00:04:31,600
A sickening and all-too-familiar sound begins to cut through the wind.

88
00:04:31,600 --> 00:04:35,000
It's the sound of a horde.

89
00:04:36,000 --> 00:04:43,000
You look around and all streets leading to this town center, or what was town center,

90
00:04:43,000 --> 00:04:47,000
begin overflowing with flesh-rotted zombies.

91
00:04:47,000 --> 00:04:49,000
This is not good.

92
00:04:49,000 --> 00:04:52,000
We thought this was the last stronghold.

93
00:04:52,000 --> 00:04:54,000
What does this mean?

94
00:04:54,000 --> 00:04:56,000
Got any magic in you, Bahamut?

95
00:04:56,000 --> 00:04:58,000
How you doing here, buddy?

96
00:04:58,000 --> 00:05:03,000
He just groans and lifts his head, but...

97
00:05:04,000 --> 00:05:09,000
Does he give me the hang loose, but his heart isn't in it?

98
00:05:09,000 --> 00:05:15,000
Yeah, that's the feel you get from the eyes rolling back in his head.

99
00:05:15,000 --> 00:05:22,000
Alright, well, if he can't really help us, I think I got something that might...

100
00:05:22,000 --> 00:05:26,000
I've had this thing for a while and I've yet to use it.

101
00:05:26,000 --> 00:05:30,000
I know the situation isn't great, but this is actually kind of exciting.

102
00:05:30,000 --> 00:05:32,000
I'm excited for you. What you got?

103
00:05:32,000 --> 00:05:40,000
Telgir roots around in his bag and you see him pull out a conch shell.

104
00:05:40,000 --> 00:05:45,000
It's two and a half feet long. Looks like it weighs a few pounds.

105
00:05:45,000 --> 00:05:50,000
And it's got a rune engraved in the side of it.

106
00:05:50,000 --> 00:05:52,000
Oh, that's pretty.

107
00:05:52,000 --> 00:05:54,000
Everybody...

108
00:05:54,000 --> 00:05:56,000
Can we get inside here?

109
00:05:56,000 --> 00:06:00,000
I don't really know how this is going to feel when I do this.

110
00:06:00,000 --> 00:06:02,000
Where are you putting this?

111
00:06:02,000 --> 00:06:04,000
Should we hold hands?

112
00:06:04,000 --> 00:06:06,000
Yeah, I don't really know.

113
00:06:06,000 --> 00:06:13,000
Maybe we all link hands and you can grab Bahamut's hands there.

114
00:06:13,000 --> 00:06:16,000
I'm going to blow on this thing and it's going to take us back.

115
00:06:16,000 --> 00:06:18,000
How do you know that?

116
00:06:18,000 --> 00:06:20,000
The horde's 15 feet away.

117
00:06:20,000 --> 00:06:22,000
I don't care, blow.

118
00:06:22,000 --> 00:06:27,000
And he takes a big lungful of breath and blows into the conch.

119
00:06:27,000 --> 00:06:29,000
What's the sound like, Tom?

120
00:06:35,000 --> 00:06:40,000
The sound of the conch of teleportation echoes out.

121
00:06:40,000 --> 00:06:42,000
As regal as it sounds.

122
00:06:42,000 --> 00:06:44,000
Super regal.

123
00:06:44,000 --> 00:06:50,000
As the dirt and frost around the heroes begins to rise, their eyes are drawn to a high point.

124
00:06:50,000 --> 00:06:54,000
A hill at the edge of the city on the horizon.

125
00:06:54,000 --> 00:07:01,000
And the dimly lit silhouettes of a tall dragonborn and a hooded gnome appear before them.

126
00:07:01,000 --> 00:07:09,000
In an instant, the spiraling energy, as if drawn from the centre of the group, pulls quickly in and the group is gone.

127
00:07:12,000 --> 00:07:14,000
It's quiet.

128
00:07:14,000 --> 00:07:17,000
Until we hear a build-up and...

129
00:07:17,000 --> 00:07:19,000
POP!

130
00:07:19,000 --> 00:07:27,000
Followed by the settling of dust to the stone floor in the sewer hideout beneath Castle Orcus.

131
00:07:27,000 --> 00:07:37,000
There's a gasp as everyone in the area turns with panic and then relief as they see your group before them.

132
00:07:37,000 --> 00:07:42,000
There's a beat and you hear from within the group.

133
00:07:42,000 --> 00:07:47,000
Holy fuck!

134
00:07:47,000 --> 00:07:58,000
Flamekins runs forward towards the group and, before Thea can say anything, leaps high in the air and wraps herself around your neck.

135
00:07:58,000 --> 00:08:11,000
They said you were back, but then you left before I came back and then I thought you might not come back, but you're back and Flint's still out and she's shaking you.

136
00:08:11,000 --> 00:08:13,000
Get your boobs out of my face!

137
00:08:13,000 --> 00:08:15,000
Put you back!

138
00:08:15,000 --> 00:08:17,000
You're back!

139
00:08:17,000 --> 00:08:18,000
Yes!

140
00:08:18,000 --> 00:08:22,000
She breaks into tears and you feel her sobbing as she hugs you.

141
00:08:22,000 --> 00:08:25,000
Oh, I hug her back tight.

142
00:08:25,000 --> 00:08:28,000
Yeah, we're back.

143
00:08:28,000 --> 00:08:41,000
Stepping out from the crowd is Leosin and a group of resistance who move towards you and begin checking your wounds and tending to the old man who you are all surrounding and appear to be protecting.

144
00:08:41,000 --> 00:08:46,000
You came back. Who's this? Come in, quick!

145
00:08:46,000 --> 00:08:49,000
Oh yeah, careful with the merchandise over here.

146
00:08:49,000 --> 00:08:50,000
Who is this?

147
00:08:50,000 --> 00:08:51,000
We found one.

148
00:08:51,000 --> 00:08:53,000
You don't recognize him?

149
00:08:53,000 --> 00:08:54,000
We have returned with a god.

150
00:08:54,000 --> 00:08:58,000
Come on, he's a really cool guy.

151
00:08:58,000 --> 00:09:03,000
Wait, you found Bahamut?

152
00:09:03,000 --> 00:09:07,000
Yeah, we wanted the best one, I assume.

153
00:09:07,000 --> 00:09:10,000
He's speechless.

154
00:09:10,000 --> 00:09:21,000
He snaps quickly to the resistance who have come and with all arms ushering them to move him back to a bed somewhere where he can rest.

155
00:09:21,000 --> 00:09:24,000
How did you?

156
00:09:24,000 --> 00:09:26,000
Do you know what this means?

157
00:09:26,000 --> 00:09:29,000
Do we have a fighting chance in this thing?

158
00:09:29,000 --> 00:09:30,000
Yeah.

159
00:09:30,000 --> 00:09:36,000
Okay, good, because that's why we did. Is this not why we're doing this?

160
00:09:36,000 --> 00:09:38,000
I feel very overwhelmed right now.

161
00:09:38,000 --> 00:09:39,000
There's a lot going on.

162
00:09:39,000 --> 00:09:42,000
Yeah, I'm just gonna hold you a little bit longer.

163
00:09:42,000 --> 00:09:51,000
Yeah, I feel like her legs are wrapped around my waist and I'm just like cradling her like, you know, like you do a toddler.

164
00:09:51,000 --> 00:09:56,000
Come in, come in, have a rest.

165
00:09:56,000 --> 00:10:00,000
I assume we were gone for the appropriate amount of time.

166
00:10:00,000 --> 00:10:04,000
There hasn't been any sort of extreme time jumps while we're gone.

167
00:10:04,000 --> 00:10:08,000
It's been a couple weeks.

168
00:10:08,000 --> 00:10:10,000
Honestly, quicker than I thought we would be.

169
00:10:10,000 --> 00:10:14,000
We unfortunately have bad news, too.

170
00:10:14,000 --> 00:10:15,000
Okay.

171
00:10:15,000 --> 00:10:17,000
We went to Luskin.

172
00:10:17,000 --> 00:10:18,000
Yes.

173
00:10:18,000 --> 00:10:19,000
And?

174
00:10:19,000 --> 00:10:21,000
And you found the Brotherhood?

175
00:10:21,000 --> 00:10:22,000
No.

176
00:10:22,000 --> 00:10:27,000
Not exactly. The tower still stands, but no one is there manning it.

177
00:10:27,000 --> 00:10:33,000
There were clues and we followed them to Icewind Dale.

178
00:10:33,000 --> 00:10:35,000
There was a god there.

179
00:10:35,000 --> 00:10:36,000
A small god.

180
00:10:36,000 --> 00:10:37,000
Aureal?

181
00:10:37,000 --> 00:10:39,000
Aureal, yes.

182
00:10:39,000 --> 00:10:40,000
Nailed it.

183
00:10:40,000 --> 00:10:45,000
They were remaining.

184
00:10:45,000 --> 00:10:48,000
They were remaining.

185
00:10:48,000 --> 00:10:52,000
Then we returned with Bahamut.

186
00:10:52,000 --> 00:10:55,000
The city had been taken by the dead.

187
00:10:55,000 --> 00:11:00,000
We would have too if...

188
00:11:00,000 --> 00:11:02,000
Fulgur had a giant shell.

189
00:11:02,000 --> 00:11:03,000
That's right, yes.

190
00:11:03,000 --> 00:11:04,000
Sorry.

191
00:11:04,000 --> 00:11:05,000
I can't breathe.

192
00:11:05,000 --> 00:11:07,000
Can you loosen up a little bit?

193
00:11:07,000 --> 00:11:09,000
Yeah, sure.

194
00:11:09,000 --> 00:11:11,000
Just going to stretch it out here.

195
00:11:11,000 --> 00:11:12,000
Totally cool.

196
00:11:12,000 --> 00:11:13,000
Playing it cool.

197
00:11:13,000 --> 00:11:14,000
It's good to see you.

198
00:11:14,000 --> 00:11:15,000
Alright.

199
00:11:15,000 --> 00:11:16,000
Fist bump.

200
00:11:16,000 --> 00:11:17,000
Where are your friends?

201
00:11:17,000 --> 00:11:18,000
That's okay.

202
00:11:18,000 --> 00:11:20,000
We don't have to explain it right now.

203
00:11:20,000 --> 00:11:22,000
I'm sure it's been explained before.

204
00:11:22,000 --> 00:11:23,000
I'll go ask somebody else.

205
00:11:23,000 --> 00:11:24,000
I'll see you in a minute.

206
00:11:24,000 --> 00:11:26,000
She's lined up pretty tight that one.

207
00:11:26,000 --> 00:11:27,000
Yes, she is.

208
00:11:27,000 --> 00:11:30,000
And also, I apologize in advance.

209
00:11:30,000 --> 00:11:32,000
You'll know why.

210
00:11:32,000 --> 00:11:35,000
Veliosan...

211
00:11:35,000 --> 00:11:36,000
What do we do now?

212
00:11:36,000 --> 00:11:39,000
We have returned Bahamut.

213
00:11:39,000 --> 00:11:45,000
We have seen other gods in a prison.

214
00:11:45,000 --> 00:11:48,000
If there's a way we can get back there, we could get them out.

215
00:11:48,000 --> 00:11:51,000
It just requires a little tradesies.

216
00:11:51,000 --> 00:11:57,000
He doesn't appear to be at peak performance, I will say.

217
00:11:57,000 --> 00:12:00,000
Yeah, there was a few there.

218
00:12:00,000 --> 00:12:05,000
And really, the only one that seemed to be high functioning was Sirik.

219
00:12:05,000 --> 00:12:12,000
Yeah, that sounds like a recipe for not ending up where we wanted to end up,

220
00:12:12,000 --> 00:12:14,000
if you were to have brought him back.

221
00:12:14,000 --> 00:12:16,000
Yeah, we tricked the trickster.

222
00:12:16,000 --> 00:12:18,000
He's probably really mad.

223
00:12:18,000 --> 00:12:23,000
He's probably pretty upset with us when we do free him.

224
00:12:23,000 --> 00:12:24,000
Great.

225
00:12:24,000 --> 00:12:25,000
If.

226
00:12:25,000 --> 00:12:28,000
I think he'll be stoked to be free, though.

227
00:12:28,000 --> 00:12:29,000
True.

228
00:12:29,000 --> 00:12:31,000
That's for another time.

229
00:12:31,000 --> 00:12:34,000
We'll worry about that when we have to cross that bridge.

230
00:12:34,000 --> 00:12:38,000
It sounds like they don't let them out quite at any...

231
00:12:38,000 --> 00:12:41,000
They don't let them out from the sounds of it, correct?

232
00:12:41,000 --> 00:12:42,000
No.

233
00:12:42,000 --> 00:12:43,000
Yes.

234
00:12:43,000 --> 00:12:45,000
I mean, that was what we were led to believe.

235
00:12:45,000 --> 00:12:51,000
Well, they take them out, but only to exterminate or destroy them.

236
00:12:52,000 --> 00:12:57,000
Yeah, Sirik said once they go out, they don't come back.

237
00:12:57,000 --> 00:13:06,000
This last couple weeks has been the most relief we have seen in more than 10 years.

238
00:13:09,000 --> 00:13:17,000
But I fear that we are creating ripples in Orcus's...

239
00:13:17,000 --> 00:13:19,000
Nipples.

240
00:13:19,000 --> 00:13:21,000
The old ripple nipple.

241
00:13:21,000 --> 00:13:22,000
Yes.

242
00:13:22,000 --> 00:13:23,000
That is bad.

243
00:13:23,000 --> 00:13:29,000
I'm glad I have this halting speech pattern where you can fill in exactly what you want to say.

244
00:13:29,000 --> 00:13:30,000
Everything I want.

245
00:13:30,000 --> 00:13:31,000
Yes.

246
00:13:31,000 --> 00:13:34,000
Ripples in his security.

247
00:13:34,000 --> 00:13:36,000
Don't say nipples again.

248
00:13:36,000 --> 00:13:37,000
She almost did.

249
00:13:37,000 --> 00:13:40,000
She was this close.

250
00:13:40,000 --> 00:13:45,000
Waves in his butt.

251
00:13:45,000 --> 00:13:46,000
Waves in his butt.

252
00:13:46,000 --> 00:13:47,000
Yep.

253
00:13:47,000 --> 00:13:48,000
See, I beat you to it.

254
00:13:48,000 --> 00:13:50,000
We got good bloops already for this episode.

255
00:13:50,000 --> 00:13:53,000
It wasn't good though.

256
00:13:56,000 --> 00:14:06,000
Did you see anyone, obviously not if they didn't come back with you, but anyone remaining in Icewind Dale where you were?

257
00:14:06,000 --> 00:14:12,000
